items.name: Signalis Style LoRA
items.description:
This is a Signalis LoRA i trained recently. I've been meaning too for months, but I had it on the backburner until recently. If you havent played Signalis, go give it a purchase! It's easily one of the best games i've ever played.

It's trained on the Cutscene images from Signalis using a variety of characters, though the characters themselves are untagged since this is a general style LoRA. Many of the images used were hand edited and color corrected in GIMP for more consistent visuals, or stitched from scrolling images to create completed character portraits. It should work great for both SFW and NSFW purposes. It was also trained on my test mix model, though, it should work on others relatively well. They wont get this exact look obviously. But some decent prompting can get you close, or maybe even get better resukts,

This was designed for txt2img generation. I have yet to test its Img2img properties, but they should work in theory? The recommended weight for the tag is somewhere around .7 if you arent trying to generate a Signalis themed character specifically.

For tags:

  • black bodysuit: Will get you the standard Signalis bodysuit look. It should work in other colors?

  • Short Black hair: Most of the characters in Signalis have it, so this will get you the closest to the Replika hair look. Though, other hair styles and colors should work fine/great.

  • face augements and eye augements: Will get you their face lines, nose squares, and ear pieces. Yes, I know its spelled "augments". I purposely spelled it differently so as to separate it from any previous concept of "augment" a model might have in it's training data.

  • Military Uniform, White Armor, black and orange armor: Will get you the minor outfits in in the data. They wont be super accurate, but they are additions that look quite nice.

  • blue eyes: Will try to get you the "Replika Eye look" to some degree.

  • bandage on arm, bandage on face: Should get you the injuries Isa Itou suffered. Though its consistency is questionable.

  • Pixilated: Goes without saying.

items.name: Photon
items.description:
Photon aims to generate photorealistic and visually appealing images effortlessly.

Recommendation for generating the first image with Photon:

  • Prompt: A simple sentence in natural language describing the image.

  • Negative: "cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2)"

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras | Steps: 20 | CFG Scale: 6

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires.fix: R-ESRGAN 4x+ | Steps: 10 | Denoising: 0.45 | Upscale x 2

  • (avoid using negative embeddings unless absolutely necessary)

From this initial point, experiment by adding positive and negative tags and adjusting the settings. Most of the sample images follow this format.

Development

The development process was somewhat chaotic but essentially:

  • It started from an old mix.

  • LORAs were trained on various topics using AI-generated photorealistic images.

  • These LORAs were mixed within the model using different weights.

  • In the midst of this mixing, hand generation broke.

  • LORAs were generated and remixed in an attempt to fix hand generation (not entirely successful).

In future versions, I will try to:

  • Completely eliminate the need for a negative prompt to generate high-quality images.

  • Fix the hand generation issue to minimize instances of poorly drawn hands.

  • Explore more automated training processes. I would love to have 5,000 or 50,000 high-quality AI-generated photorealistic images for training purposes.

I hope you enjoy using it as much as I enjoyed creating it! If you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to share. Have fun creating amazing images! 🎨

items.name: Meru The Succubus Realistic
items.description:
This was my attempt at creating Meru the succubus but centered around being more realistic. I think the results turned out pretty great, and you will be able to re-create my results if you follow my workflow. Please read it first, before asking me, why you are not able to make the same images. Copying the generation data from example images wont yield the same results because they are not directly from txt2img.

Settings

First of all the settings. Don't use a CFG scale over 7 or else you will be getting artifacts. I found 6 to be pretty good. Use this prompt for the best results:

<lora:MeruSuccubus:0.8>, merusuccubus, (red skin), colored skin, (yellow eyes, glowing eyes), horns, (demon tail), choker, bangs,

Very important to also include this in the negative or else you will be getting extra nipples and a lot of moles:

(multiple mole:1.2), (multiple nipples:1.2),

Steps: 32-37

CFG: 5-7

Resolution: 512x768

My full prompt:

photorealistic, (hyperrealistic:1.2), beautiful, masterpiece, best quality, extremely detailed face, perfect lighting , <lora:MeruSuccubus:0.8>, merusuccubus, (red skin), colored skin, (yellow eyes, glowing eyes), horns, (demon tail), choker, bangs,

negative:

(worst quality, low quality:1.4), (monochrome), zombie, watermark, username,patreon username, patreon logo, (extra fingers, deformed hands, polydactyl:1.5),(multiple mole:1.2), (multiple nipples:1.2),

Workflow

All the example images were created with this workflow:

1:

First generate a txt2img which you like (The quality wont be sharp ofc). You can do a hiresfix if you want to.

2:

Send the image to img2img. Here i set the resolution as 936x1400 (Width x Height) because that is what my pc can handle. Set the denoise strength between 0.35-0.5

3:

Send the image you like to inpainting. Start inpainting all the features like the face, body, clothes, hands etc..

4:

Send to extra and upscale the image with your favorite upscaler. I used 4x_fatal_anime

items.name: Ellie (TLOU part 1) Clean Lora
items.description:
This is my own version of Ellie from The last of us (part 1).

What's special about this LORA is that every training images are generated in Blender with original game model with complete white background, which results in every generations being constant and stable in quality. Thus naming it, CLEAN LORA.

Images with most popular camera angles are prioritized in learning with minor camera angles still being learnt but with less repetition. Ensuring most generations resulting in good camera shots. 35 repetitions are portrait and upper body shots. 25 are full body shots. 15 are extreme angles and sitting, and character looking away.

3 bake versions are uploaded, AnyLora and Stable Diffusion v1.5 base. And then GhostMix v3 bake which is for using with GhostMix mainly.

Prompts:

TLOU_EW is an optional token that can be used in prompts but unnecessary. Use this to get your image closer to trained images.

MUST PLACE (bruise, dirty:1.3) in NEGATIVES to produce clean face without artifacts.

Recommended LORA strength = 0.5 ~ 0.6

Machine Learning Stats:

Dimension = 512 x 768

(25 images x 35 repeats = 1015 steps)

+ (17 images x 25 repeats = 425 steps)

+ (21 images x 15 repeats = 315 steps)

/3 batch process = 585 steps per epoch

585 steps x 22 epoch = 12870 total steps

About V5.0:

Why is there no V4.0? Because I am not very satisfied with the 4.0 version, half of it was rejected by me...so I jumped directly to 5.0.

Some friends reported that when using the V3.0 version, it is not easy to make a full-body picture. After the weight is increased, it is difficult to control the movement of the characters. In addition, there are problems with the deterioration of the hands and the excessive impact on the background.

So this version is mainly used to fix these three problems.

V5.0 has improved in these three aspects, and it cannot be said to be a perfect solution, but at least it will not be so strenuous to adjust.

For example, no matter what base film you use, if you increase the weight of (full body), for example, to more than 1.7, there is a high probability that a full body image will be displayed.

About V5.0:

Why is there no V4.0? Because I am not very satisfied with the 4.0 version, half of it was rejected by me...so I jumped directly to 5.0.

Some friends reported that when using the V3.0 version, it is not easy to make a full-body picture. After the weight is increased, it is difficult to control the movement of the characters. In addition, there are problems with the deterioration of the hands and the excessive impact on the background.

So this version is mainly used to fix these three problems.

V5.0 has improved in these three aspects, and it cannot be said to be a perfect solution, but at least it will not be so strenuous to adjust.

For example, no matter what base film you use, if you increase the weight of (full body), for example, to more than 1.7, there is a high probability that a full body image will be displayed.

When using this version, the weight can be relatively slightly larger. 0.65 is a critical point. Different weights have different effects.

V3 version:

Compared to the V2 version, improvements are as follows:

Friends who have used this model must have found that the V2 version does still have a certain degree of generalization problem.

Although faces and hair can easily change, the body's movement, background, etc., can be affected by the LORA. I also discovered this problem in my tests. So, I adjusted the model as quickly as possible.

I made major adjustments to the original dataset and adjusted parameters such as the learning rate, and finely tuned the weight of the hierarchical training.

Now, this problem is basically non-existent. I didn't encounter any problems in my experiments. It is more convenient to use than previous versions.

I will update according to the actual use situation. If you encounter any problems in use, please give feedback in time.

V3バージョン：

V2バージョンと比較して、次のような改善が行われました：

このモデルを使用した人々は、V2バージョンがある程度の一般化問題をまだ抱えていることに気づいたでしょう。

顔や髪の毛などは容易に変化しますが、体の動きや背景などはLORAの影響を受けます。この問題は私もテスト中に発見しました。だから私はできるだけ早くモデルを調整しました。

元のデータセットに大幅な調整を行い、学習率などの各パラメータを調整し、階層型トレーニングの重みを微調整しました。

今では、この問題はほとんど存在しなくなりました。私の実験では何も問題に遭遇しなかった。それは以前のバージョンよりも使いやすいです。

私は実際の使用状況に応じて更新します。使用中に何か問題が発生した場合は、すぐにフィードバックをお願いします。

用过本模型的小伙伴们肯定也能发现，V2版本其实还是存在一定程度的泛化问题。

这个问题其实我在测试中也发现了。

所以我尽快的对模型进行了调整。

大幅度对原始数据集进行调整，对学习率等各个参数都进行了调整，精细化调节了分层训练的权重。

现在，这方面的问题基本上就没有了，我在实验中没有遇到什么问题。使用起来更加方便，比之前的版本都要好用。

modelVersions.description:
Compared to the V1 version, there has been a significant upgrade, with better generalization and greater ease of use.

The main upgrades are:

  1. Change of dataset: all datasets use 8K ultra-high-definition images compressed and vectorized, further enhancing stylization (steampunk + sci-fi + female body shaping). Using the new version of Photoshop, all images are manually cut out and resolution detail enhanced + hand correction, greatly improving the quality of the dataset.

  2. Regularization: extensive use of high-quality images for regularization processing, improving the model's generalization.

  3. Calculation of learning rate and replacement of the new version of the optimizer, further reducing the LOSS value.

  4. Use of layer settings, reducing the weight of the face and other positions, making it easier to use.

  5. Change of base model: chose a base model that better suits this model.

  6. Even at low weights, it can have a certain impact on the screen characters, making it easy to use with many other LORAs without error. Also, at high weights, it is less likely to degrade the image. Weights can be between 0.2-0.9.

The following are some comparison images from testing, please refer to them. (Comparison of V1 version and V2 version images in the case of almost unchanged tags)

Generation Suggestions:

The trigger word for the V2 version is: cbpkv2 When using it, you can add various keywords according to your preference, such as:

breasts full body looking at viewer medium breasts solo standing kneeling small breasts ass

For the V2 version, it is recommended to turn on high-resolution correction, keep the redrawing range within 0.5, and turn on CFG correction. Adjust the CFG Scale Scheduler to Half Cosine Up, and the MVOTCSS to 3.5.

This model has a good generality and has been proven to perform well in various models. The large models I often use are: theallysmix, v80, perfectworld, revanimated, etc.

I feel that there is still room for optimization in this model, and I plan to continue optimizing this model.

V1バージョンと比較して、大きなアップグレードがあり、汎用性が向上し、より使いやすくなりました。

主なアップグレードは以下の通りです：

  1. データセットの変更：すべてのデータセットは8K超高解像度の画像を圧縮してベクトル化処理し、スタイル化（スチームパンク+SF+女性の体型）を強化しました。新しいバージョンのPhotoshopを使用して、すべての画像を手作業で切り取り、解像度の詳細を強化し、手の修正を行うことで、データセットの品質を大幅に向上させました。

  2. 正則化：多数の高品質画像を使用して正則化処理を行い、モデルの汎用性を向上させました。

  3. 学習率を計算し、新しいバージョンの最適化器に変更し、LOSS値をさらに低減しました。

  4. レイヤー化設定を採用し、顔などの位置の重みを下げ、使いやすさを向上させました。

  5. ベースモデルの変更：このモデルにより適合したベースモデルを選びました。

  6. 低い重みでも画面のキャラクターに一定の影響を与えることができ、他の多くのLORAと一緒に使用する際にエラーが発生することなく、高い重みでも画像が劣化しにくくなりました。重みは0.2-0.9の範囲で可能です。

V2バージョンでは、高解像度修正をオンにすること、再描画の範囲を0.5以下にすること、CFG修正をオンにすることをおすすめします。CFG Scale SchedulerはHalf Cosine Upに、MVOTCSSは3.5に調整してください。

このモデルは汎用性が高く、各モデルで良好なパフォーマンスを示すことが実証されています。 私がよく使用する大型モデルは：theallysmix,v80,perfectworld,revanimatedなど。

このモデルにはまだ改善の余地があると感じています。このモデルの最適化を続けるつもりです。

相比V1版本，有了比较重大的升级，泛化性更好，更加方便易用了。

主要的升级有：

1、 更换数据集，数据集均采用8K 超高清图片压缩+矢量化处理，进一步加强了风格化（蒸汽朋克+科幻+女体塑型），使用新版本的PS对所有图片进行人工抠图和提升分辨率细节+修手处理，大幅度提高数据集的质量。

2、 正则化，使用大量高质量图片进行正则化处理，提高模型的泛化性。

3、 测算学习率并更换了新版本的优化器，进一步降低了LOSS值。

4、 采用分层设置，降低了脸部等位置的权重，更加易于使用。

5、 更换底模，挑选了更加适合本模型的底模。

6、 低权重即可对画面人物产生一定的影响，方便搭配更多其他LORA一起使用而不会出现报错。同时在高权重时也不容易出现劣化的画面。权重在0.2-0.9之间均可。
